12 Subject to the hearing provisions of § 5–312 of this subtitle, the Board, on the
13 affirmative vote of a majority of its members then serving, may deny a license to any
14 applicant, reprimand any licensee, or suspend or revoke a license if the applicant or
15 licensee:
16 (1) Fraudulently or deceptively obtains or attempts to obtain a license for
17 the applicant or licensee or for another;
18 (2) Fraudulently or deceptively uses a license;
19 (3) Violates any provision of this title or any regulations adopted under this
20 title;
21 (4) Refuses, withholds from, denies, or discriminates against an individual
22 with regard to the provision of professional service for which the licensee is licensed and
23 qualified to render because the individual is HIV positive;
24 (5) Commits fraud or deceit in the practice of dietetics;
25 (6) Is convicted of or pleads nolo contendere to a felony or to a crime
26 involving moral turpitude, whether or not any appeal or other proceeding is pending to
27 have the conviction or plea set aside;
28 (7) Obtains or attempts to obtain a fee through fraud or misrepresentation;
29 (8) Employs any [person] INDIVIDUAL to practice dietetics whose license
30 or certificate to practice a health occupation under this article has been suspended;

16 HOUSE BILL 1420
1 (9) Uses or promotes or causes the use of any misleading, deceiving, or
2 untruthful advertising matter, or promotional literature, testimonial, guarantee, warranty,
3 label, brand, insignia, or other representation;
4 (10) Commits any act of unprofessional conduct, as defined by the rules and
5 regulations of the Board, or violates the code of ethics adopted by the Board;
6 (11) Provides professional services while:
7 (i) Under the influence of alcohol; or
8 (ii) Using any narcotic or controlled dangerous substance, as defined
