5 subsection is returned to the Board as undeliverable, the Board shall send to the wholesale
6 distributor permit holder a renewal notice by first–class mail to the last known address of
7 the permit holder.
8 (4) A renewal notice sent under this subsection shall state:
9 (i) The date on which the current wholesale distributor permit
10 expires;
11 (ii) The date by which the renewal application must be received by
12 the Board for the renewal to be issued and mailed before the current wholesale distributor
13 permit expires; and
14 (iii) The amount of the renewal fee.
15 (5) Before a wholesale distributor permit expires, a wholesale distributor
16 permit holder periodically may renew it for an additional 2–year term, if the wholesale
17 distributor permit holder:
18 (i) Otherwise is entitled to a wholesale distributor permit;
19 (ii) Pays to the Board a renewal fee set by the Board; and
20 (iii) Submits to the Board a renewal application on the form that the
21 Board requires.
22 (6) (i) The renewal application form shall set forth the information that
23 the wholesale distributor provided under § 12–6C–05 of this subtitle.
24 (ii) Within 30 days after receiving the form, the wholesale
25 distributor shall identify and state under oath to the Board all changes or corrections to the
26 information that was provided under § 12–6C–05 of this subtitle.
27 (7) The Board shall renew the wholesale distributor permit of a wholesale
28 distributor permit holder who meets the requirements of this subtitle and any regulations
29 adopted under this subtitle.
30 (8) IF A WHOLESALE DISTRIBUTOR IS LOCATED OUTSIDE THE STATE,
31 THE DESIGNATED REPRESENTATIVE AND IMMEDIATE SUPERVISOR OF THE
32 DESIGNATED REPRESENTATIVE OF THE PERMIT HOLDER SHALL SUBMIT TO A
33 CRIMINAL HISTORY RECORDS CHECK IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 12–6C–05.1 OF THIS
34 SUBTITLE BEFORE THE PERMIT MAY BE RENEWED.

